        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 3 at 3:03PM MDT until August 3 at 3:30PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 302 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 11 miles north of
Sharon Springs, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
northeastern Wallace County.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
